  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Place your<strong> creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> (in its packaging!) in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> (this softens the naturally hard cream)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1612977991488-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1612977991488-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1612977991488-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1612977991488-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1612977991488-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>diced</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and cook, covered, for 3-5 min or until beginning to soften and brown slightly</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small cubes</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1612978000541-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1612978000541-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1612978000541-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1612978000541-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1612978000541-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for a further 4-6 min</p><p>Whilst everything is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>thyme leaves </strong>from their stalks and chop them finely, discard the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1612978005882-x200.jpg",
