            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, most<strong> </strong>of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> (save some for garnish!) and your<strong> bay leaf[ves]</strong> to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Stir and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan, cover, and bring to the boil</p>",
